# Floom CLI — Cursor integration

Use the `floom` CLI to scaffold and deploy AI apps to Floom.

Docs: https://floom.dev/docs
Examples: https://github.com/floomhq/floom/tree/main/examples

## Install (if not present)

```bash
git clone --depth 1 https://github.com/floomhq/floom.git ~/.floom/repo
export PATH="$HOME/.floom/repo/cli/floom/bin:$PATH"
```

## Auth

```bash
floom login
# token page: https://floom.dev/home
# non-interactive: floom auth login --token=floom_agent_...
```

Or set `FLOOM_API_KEY` as an env var.

## Typical workflow

```bash
# scaffold a floom.yaml
floom init

# preview the deploy request without sending
floom deploy --dry-run

# publish
floom deploy

# check your apps and recent runs
floom status
```

## floom.yaml shape (OpenAPI app)

```yaml
name: My App
slug: my-app
description: One-sentence description.
type: proxied
openapi_spec_url: https://example.com/openapi.json
visibility: private
manifest_version: "2.0"
```

## floom.yaml shape (custom Python app)

```yaml
name: My App
slug: my-app
description: One-sentence description.
category: custom
runtime: python
actions:
  run:
    label: Run
    description: One-sentence description.
    inputs:
      - {name: input, label: Input, type: textarea, required: true}
    outputs:
      - {name: result, label: Result, type: text}
python_dependencies: []
secrets_needed: [GEMINI_API_KEY]
manifest_version: "2.0"
```

## Slug rules

- lowercase, hyphens only
- matches `^[a-z0-9][a-z0-9-]{0,47}$`

## Auth resolution order

1. `FLOOM_API_KEY` env var (+ optional `FLOOM_API_URL`)
2. `~/.floom/config.json` written by `floom auth`
3. Legacy `~/.claude/floom-skill-config.json`

## Account context and secrets

```bash
floom account context get
floom account context set-user --json '{"name":"Federico"}'
floom account context set-workspace --json '{"company":{"name":"Floom"}}'
floom run <slug> '<inputs-json>' --use-context
floom account secrets list
floom account secrets set GEMINI_API_KEY --value "$GEMINI_API_KEY"
```

Never print secret values. `secrets list` returns metadata, not plaintext.

## Error codes

| HTTP | Meaning | Action |
|------|---------|--------|
| 401 | bad token | `floom auth logout` then `floom login` |
| 409 | slug taken | pick a different slug, update floom.yaml |
| 5xx | server error | retry once; check https://floom.dev/status |
